==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prosopopœia
<hw>Pros`o*po*p⟦oe⟧"ia</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <?/; <grk>pro`swpon</grk> a face, a person + <?/ to make.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure by which things are represented as
persons, or by which things inanimate are spoken of as animated beings;
also, a figure by which an absent person is introduced as speaking, or a
deceased person is represented as alive and present. It includes
<xex>personification</xex>, but is more extensive in its
signification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prosopulmonata</ent>⟦br⟧
